#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:2
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:5
msgid "Command line options and configuration file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:7
msgid ""
"You can get help on command line options and values in INI-style "
"configurations files by using the general help option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:10
msgid "pytest -h   # prints options _and_ config file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:14
msgid ""
"This will display command line and configuration file settings which were "
"registered by installed plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:21
msgid "Initialization: determining rootdir and inifile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:25
msgid ""
"pytest determines a ``rootdir`` for each test run which depends on the "
"command line arguments (specified test files, paths) and on the existence of "
"*ini-files*.  The determined ``rootdir`` and *ini-file* are printed as part "
"of the pytest header during startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:30
msgid "Here's a summary what ``pytest`` uses ``rootdir`` for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:32
msgid ""
"Construct *nodeids* during collection; each test is assigned a unique "
"*nodeid* which is rooted at the ``rootdir`` and takes in account full path, "
"class name, function name and parametrization (if any)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:36
msgid ""
"Is used by plugins as a stable location to store project/test run specific "
"information; for example, the internal :ref:`cache <cache>` plugin creates a "
"``.pytest_cache`` subdirectory in ``rootdir`` to store its cross-test run "
"state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:40
msgid ""
"Important to emphasize that ``rootdir`` is **NOT** used to modify ``sys."
"path``/``PYTHONPATH`` or influence how modules are imported. See :ref:"
"`pythonpath` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:43
msgid ""
"``--rootdir=path`` command-line option can be used to force a specific "
"directory. The directory passed may contain environment variables when it is "
"used in conjunction with ``addopts`` in a ``pytest.ini`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:48
msgid "Finding the ``rootdir``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:50
msgid "Here is the algorithm which finds the rootdir from ``args``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:52
msgid ""
"determine the common ancestor directory for the specified ``args`` that are "
"recognised as paths that exist in the file system. If no such paths are "
"found, the common ancestor directory is set to the current working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:56
msgid ""
"look for ``pytest.ini``, ``tox.ini`` and ``setup.cfg`` files in the ancestor "
"directory and upwards.  If one is matched, it becomes the ini-file and its "
"directory becomes the rootdir."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:60
msgid ""
"if no ini-file was found, look for ``setup.py`` upwards from the common "
"ancestor directory to determine the ``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:63
msgid ""
"if no ``setup.py`` was found, look for ``pytest.ini``, ``tox.ini`` and "
"``setup.cfg`` in each of the specified ``args`` and upwards. If one is "
"matched, it becomes the ini-file and its directory becomes the rootdir."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:67
msgid ""
"if no ini-file was found, use the already determined common ancestor as root "
"directory. This allows the use of pytest in structures that are not part of "
"a package and don't have any particular ini-file configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:71
msgid ""
"If no ``args`` are given, pytest collects test below the current working "
"directory and also starts determining the rootdir from there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:0
msgid "warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:74
msgid ""
"custom pytest plugin commandline arguments may include a path, as in "
"``pytest --log-output ../../test.log args``. Then ``args`` is mandatory, "
"otherwise pytest uses the folder of test.log for rootdir determination (see "
"also `issue 1435 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1435>`_). A "
"dot ``.`` for referencing to the current working directory is also possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:81
msgid ""
"Note that an existing ``pytest.ini`` file will always be considered a match, "
"whereas ``tox.ini`` and ``setup.cfg`` will only match if they contain a "
"``[pytest]`` or ``[tool:pytest]`` section, respectively. Options from "
"multiple ini-files candidates are never merged - the first one wins "
"(``pytest.ini`` always wins, even if it does not contain a ``[pytest]`` "
"section)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:87
msgid "The ``config`` object will subsequently carry these attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:89
msgid "``config.rootdir``: the determined root directory, guaranteed to exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:91
msgid "``config.inifile``: the determined ini-file, may be ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:93
msgid ""
"The rootdir is used as a reference directory for constructing test addresses "
"(\"nodeids\") and can be used also by plugins for storing per-testrun "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:97
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:99
msgid "pytest path/to/testdir path/other/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:103
msgid ""
"will determine the common ancestor as ``path`` and then check for ini-files "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:106
msgid ""
"# first look for pytest.ini files\n"
"path/pytest.ini\n"
"path/setup.cfg  # must also contain [tool:pytest] section to match\n"
"path/tox.ini    # must also contain [pytest] section to match\n"
"pytest.ini\n"
"... # all the way down to the root\n"
"\n"
"# now look for setup.py\n"
"path/setup.py\n"
"setup.py\n"
"... # all the way down to the root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:127
msgid "How to change command line options defaults"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:129
msgid ""
"It can be tedious to type the same series of command line options every time "
"you use ``pytest``.  For example, if you always want to see detailed info on "
"skipped and xfailed tests, as well as have terser \"dot\" progress output, "
"you can write it into a configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:134
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini or tox.ini\n"
"# setup.cfg files should use [tool:pytest] section instead\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -ra -q"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:141
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can set a ``PYTEST_ADDOPTS`` environment variable to add "
"command line options while the environment is in use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:144
msgid "export PYTEST_ADDOPTS=\"-v\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:148
msgid ""
"Here's how the command-line is built in the presence of ``addopts`` or the "
"environment variable:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:150
msgid "<pytest.ini:addopts> $PYTEST_ADDOPTS <extra command-line arguments>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:154
msgid "So if the user executes in the command-line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:156
msgid "pytest -m slow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:160
msgid "The actual command line executed is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:162
msgid "pytest -ra -q -v -m slow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:166
msgid ""
"Note that as usual for other command-line applications, in case of "
"conflicting options the last one wins, so the example above will show "
"verbose output because ``-v`` overwrites ``-q``."
msgstr ""

